fields.title: Inclusion Tags
fields.summary: One way of including a template inside another is with the include template tag. We’ve used this to
fields.content: This is very simple to implement, but its main drawback is that included templates can only access variables that are already in the including template’s context. That means any extra variables need to be passed in from the calling view, so if it’s a template that’s used in lots of places you’ll be repeating the data-loading code in lots of different views. By using an inclusion tag, you can query for extra data inside your template tag function, which can then be used to render a template.
